## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="ffc43-135">Quando viene aggiunta una serie in fase di progettazione e fase di esecuzione, viene assegnato automaticamente da "Predefinito" <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartArea> oggetto o la prima area grafico disponibile il <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartAreaCollection> se "Predefinito" non esiste.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ffc43-135">When a series is added at both design time and run time, it is automatically assigned to the "Default" <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartArea> object, or the first available chart area in the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartAreaCollection> if "Default" does not exist.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ffc43-136">Impostare questa proprietà su una stringa di lunghezza zero se non si desidera la serie da tracciare.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ffc43-136">Set this property to a zero-length string if you do not want the series to be plotted.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
  
```vb  
' Create a new legend and associate three series with the legend.  
Public Sub CreateSecondLegend()  
    ' Attach the first series to a chart area.  
    Chart1.Series["Series1"].ChartArea = "Chart Area 1";  
  
    ' Attach the second series to a chart area.  
    Chart1.Series["Series2"].ChartArea = "Chart Area 2";  
  
End Sub 'CreateSecondLegend  
```  
  
```csharp  
// Create a new legend and associate three series with the legend.  
public void CreateSecondLegend()  
{  
     // Attach the first series to a chart area.  
     Chart1.Series["Series1"].ChartArea = "Chart Area 1";  
  
     // Attach the second series to a chart area.  
     Chart1.Series["Series2"].ChartArea = "Chart Area 2";  
  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="ffc43-220">Ottiene o imposta il colore dell'ombreggiatura di una serie, che può essere un qualsiasi valore ARGB (alfa, rosso, verde, blu) valido.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ffc43-220">Gets or sets the shadow color of a series, which can be to any valid ARGB (alpha, red, green, blue) value.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ffc43-221">Il valore alfa è utilizzabile per ottenere un effetto di ombreggiatura realistica. Provare a usare un valore di colore della "128,0,0,0" per le ombreggiature.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ffc43-221">The alpha value can be used to achieve a realistic shadow effect; try using a color value of "128,0,0,0" for shadows.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ffc43-222">Per implementare un'ombreggiatura, impostare il <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Series.ShadowOffset%2A> proprietà un valore diverso da zero (0).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ffc43-222">To implement a shadow, set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Series.ShadowOffset%2A> property to a value other than zero (0).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
  
```  
' Set series shadow color and offset  
Public Sub SetSeriesShadow()  
     Chart1.Series("Default"}.ShadowColor = Color.Blue  
     Chart1.Series("Default"}.ShadowOffset = 2  
End Sub 'SetSeriesShadow  
```  
  
```csharp  
// Set series shadow color and offset   
public void SetSeriesShadow()  
{      
    Chart1.Series("Default"}.ShadowColor = Color.Blue;  
    Chart1.Series["Default"].ShadowOffset = 2;  
}  
```
